mike_bn 2025-07-14 11:45 a.m.
PAPERLESS ORDER

# FINAL JUDGEMENT #

This matter was brought before the Court on the 2nd of July, 2025. The Defendant was summoned, and ordered to appear before this Court within five (5) days, on the 3rd of July, 2025. The summons was verified by testimony alongside a photograph. Defendant is well aware of these proceedings, but indicated that they are on vacation, thus unable to participate. The Court finds this excuse to be weak, as the Defendant has had every opportunity to hire a lawyer to appear before them in these proceedings, but failed to do so. Thus, the Defendant by his own will forced this court to find him in default judgement. Awards are assessed as follows:

- The court enters a declaratory judgement that the defendant is liable for battery, assault, and negligence.
- The court awards Plaintiff atwilled punitive damages in the amount of $50,000 as for battery.
- The court awards Plaintiff atwilled punitive damages in the amount of $30,000 as for assault.
- The court awards Plaintiff atwilled punitive damages in the amount of $60,000 as for negligence.
- The court awards Plaintiff EffortlessBrit punitive damages in the amount of $50,000 as for battery.
- The court awards Plaintiff EffortlessBrit punitive damages in the amount of $30,000 as for assault.
- The court awards Plaintiff EffortlessBrit punitive damages in the amount of $60,000 as for negligence.

Defendant has five (5) days to satisfy this judgement, or make an effort/plan to satisfy the judgement. Failure to do so will result in the Defendant being held in contempt, and jailed indefinitely until he complies.

So ordered.
